# Backend Rules

## Runtime & Dependencies
- Python **3.13+** required
- Package manager: **uv** ‚Äî `pyproject.toml` is the source of truth, never create a `requirements.txt`
- To add a package: `uv add <package>` (updates pyproject.toml automatically)
- To run: `uv run uvicorn main:app --reload` from `backend/`
- Dev dependencies live in `[dependency-groups] dev = [...]` in pyproject.toml

## FastAPI Conventions
- All route handlers are `async`
- All request/response bodies use **Pydantic models** ‚Äî no raw `dict` returns from endpoints
- Routers live in `backend/routes/` and are included in `main.py` via `app.include_router()`
- Lifespan events (startup/shutdown) use the `@asynccontextmanager` lifespan pattern ‚Äî not deprecated `@app.on_event`
- CORS is already configured in `main.py` for `http://localhost:5173` ‚Äî do not add duplicate middleware

## Mistral SDK
- Client: `from mistralai import Mistral` ‚Äî this is the v1+ SDK
- Always use `client.chat.complete(...)` ‚Äî not the old `client.chat()` method
- Default model constant: `"mistral-small-latest"` (defined in `_resolve_model()` in `routes/dialogue.py`)
- `labs-mistral-small-creative` is commented out ‚Äî leave it commented unless asked
- `completion.choices[0].message.content` can be `None` ‚Äî always guard with `or "*(silence)*"`
- Keep `max_tokens=200` for NPC dialogue to control latency and cost

## NPC & Agent System (`backend/agents/npcs.py`)
- `NPC` dataclass: agent NPCs that call Mistral ‚Äî has `system_prompt`, `secret`, `knowledge`
- `Person` dataclass: background NPCs ‚Äî has `greeting` only, **no Mistral calls ever**
- `QuestClue.secret` is internal only ‚Äî **never send `secret` to the frontend**, only `hint`
- `QUEST_0` is the hardcoded fallback quest ‚Äî always keep it valid and importable
- `NPC_COLORS` drives frontend zone border colours ‚Äî keep in sync if adding categories
- System prompts: English with French Belle √âpoque flavour, anachronism boundary ~1910

## W&B Integration
- W&B run is initialised in `main.py` lifespan ‚Äî do not call `wandb.init()` inside route handlers
- All `wandb.log()` calls must be wrapped in `try/except Exception: pass` ‚Äî W&B must never crash the game
- Check `if wandb.run is None: return` before logging in helper functions

## Conversation History
- In-memory dict `_history` in `routes/dialogue.py` keyed by `"{session_id}:{npc_id}"`
- System prompt is prepended fresh each call ‚Äî do NOT store it in `_history`
- History is unbounded for now (hackathon scope) ‚Äî do not add trimming unless asked

## Environment Variables
- Loaded via `python-dotenv` from `backend/.env`
- Required: `MISTRAL_API_KEY`
- Optional: `FINETUNED_MODEL_ID`, `WANDB_API_KEY`, `WANDB_PROJECT`, `ELEVENLABS_API_KEY`
- Never hardcode keys ‚Äî always use `os.environ["KEY"]` (required) or `os.getenv("KEY", default)` (optional)
